star  aMichael Lentz' opus magnum "Schattenfroh" ist eine Zumutung: Umfang und Komplexität stellen der Lektüre immense Hindernisse in den Weg. Aber zugleich erhebt der Text den Anspruch, eine umfassende literarische Enzyklopädie zu sein. Er stellt sich in die Reihe der großen Avantgardetexte seit Joyce. Der vorliegende Band sondiert erste Zugänge und unternimmt Versuche, Lektürewege in die äußerst dichte Textur zu bahnen.  aMichael Lentz’ opus magnum Schattenfroh is an imposition: its length and complexity create obstacles to reading. But, at the same time, the text lays claim to the status of extensive literary encyclopedia. It is another chapter in the history of great avant-gardist texts since modernity. This volume attempts to unlock this extremely dense text of this prose, paving the way for future readings.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 4aEnzyklopädie. 4aLentz, Michael. 4aProsa. 4aSchattenfroh.  aEncyclopaedia.  aLentz, Michael.  aSchattenfroh.  aprose.1 aAngerer, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBraun, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedrich, Hans-Edwin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeman, Emmanuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeman, Emmanuel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMoser, Natalie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNiehaus, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSata, Lehel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScheffold, Maximilian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmitz-Emans, Monika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/voc